<body>
  <h1 class="header">Overview of the experiment</h1>
  <h1 id="welcome"></h1>
  <p id="caution">Please note that you need to be a frequent user of Spotify, otherwise the system cannot generate recommendations for you.</p>
  <h2>Introduction</h2>
  <p style="white-space:pre;">In this experiment, we use the Spotify API to design this music recommender system. In the system, you can firs select up to five of your favorite artists. The system also allows you to modify 5 different parameters, and based on your selected artists
    and the parameters, it provides you with suggestions of songs. In this study, we aim to get your perceived quality of different visualisations, and measure your cognitive load while interacting with our system. This page gives an overview of what
    you can expect of this experiment.

  </p>
  <h2>Steps</h2>
  <p>This experiment concludes six different steps:
    <ul>
      <li>Demographic questionnaire</li>
      <li>First interface with a task</li>
      <li>Post-task questionnaire</li>
      <li>Second interface with a task</li>
      <li>Post-task questionnaire</li>
      <li>Post evaluation questions</li>
    </ul>
  </p>
  <h2>Your task</h2>
  <p>
    <ol>
      <li>Read carefully what you need to do</li>
      <li>Select some of your favorite artists</li>
      <li>Adjust parameters</li>
      <li>Click on the button to calculate recommendations</li>
      <li>Listen to a song</li>
      <li>Like or dislike a song</li>
      <li>Repeat step 2 to 5 until you like 9 songs</li>
      <li>Click on the button to save recommendations</li>
      <li>Fill in the questionnaire</li>
    </ol>
  </p><button id="overview" class="ripple button">Start experiment</button></body>

